As of Monday, a total of 1,101,827 Nigerians have been vaccinated with the first dose in the first phase of the COVID-19 vaccination, according to the latest data from the National Primary Health Care Development Agency (NPHCDA). Also, 11 states are yet to reach the 50 per cent target mark of the first dose of COVID-19 vaccine. This brings the proportion of those vaccinated to 54.8 per cent. The states are Abia (31.8), Akwa Ibom (36.5), Anambra (28.2), Bayelsa (48.3), Ebonyi (38.8), Enugu (37.7), FCT (44.9), Imo (48.3), Rivers (38.7), Sokoto (34.5), Taraba (31.9).